<h1>Configuration</h1>

<p>
  All settings of GuitarGeeksVR are stored in its configurations folder which is located in:
  <ul>
    <li><code>&#37;LOCALAPPDATA&#37;/GuitarGeeksVR</code> on Windows</li>
    <li><code>~/Library/Application Support/.GuitarGeeksVR</code> on Mac OS X</li>
    <li><code>~/.GuitarGeeksVR</code> on Linux</li>
  </ul>
  GuitarGeeksVR does not modify the registry nor does it require any kind of installation.
  The default settings are created the first time you run GuitarGeeksVR.
</p>
<p>
  The main settings are stored in a file called <code>settings.json</code>.
  The following example shows a <code>settings.json</code> which sets two tab folders to be monitored and adds custom soundfont:
</p>
  <div class="codewrap">
      <% code("json") do %>
{
  "watchedTabFolders" : [ "/home/yourname/.GuitarGeeksVR/tabs",
                          "/home/yourname/some/other/path" ],
  "backgroundColors" : [ "080F5EFF",
                         "222222FF",
                         "002A36FF",
                         "1F2229FF",
                         "042129FF",
                         "4997D0FF",
                         "EEEEEEFF" ],
  "headRollThreshold" : 30.0,
  "soundfont" : "/home/yourname/.GuitarGeeksVR/soundfonts/Unison.SF2"
}<% end %>
  </div>
<p>
  To specify path names it should not matter if you use <code>/</code> or <code>\\</code> as path separator.
  GuitarGeeksVR does not scan the tab folders when it starts -- scanning huge tab folders can be slow and this would mean very long load times.
  When you have added new tabs to your folders, You have to press the "rescan" button to force the scan.
</p>

